2 of 2: and how long they remained in the program so we better understand how to serve them.
1 of 2: But today is about understanding those families in need. Who they are, what has brought them to the program...
2 of 2: that help feed Hoosiers in my district & provide support to families & children in need.
1 of 2: While I recognize the gov't role in this process, there are local orgs like St. Margaret's House & the Food Bank of northern IN...
That's why its so important that this sbcmte focus our efforts on understanding how SNAP can best serve families & children across the U.S.
2 of 2: and specifically its recipients and find unmet needs and areas of overlap.
1 of 2: It is my hope & expectation that this sbcmte will explore & gain a better understanding of the entire program...
& when I read that 1 in 6 Americans is hungry, it reaffirmed my commitment to ensure no child or adult endures what I've seen others go thru
I know what starvation looks like & how it affects families & communities.
